### Describe the bug

SSIA

It appears that there are cases where `PropertyValueBuffer.assignParameter` is not called for properties defined in this way.
https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-module-kotlin/issues/1153#issuecomment-4363639816

### Version Information

- 2.21
- 3.2.0-SNAPSHOT

### Reproduction

It appeared that omitting `@JsonProperty(access = JsonProperty.Access.WRITE_ONLY)` did not change the error message.

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import tools.jackson.databind.cfg.MapperConfig;
import tools.jackson.databind.introspect.*;
import tools.jackson.databind.json.JsonMapper;
import tools.jackson.databind.module.SimpleModule;

import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;

public class GitHub1153JavaTest {
    private static final String CONSTRUCTOR_PARAM_NAME = "uri";

    public static class JavaObjectWithRedactedField {
        private final String uri;

        @JsonProperty(value = CONSTRUCTOR_PARAM_NAME, access = JsonProperty.Access.READ_ONLY)
        public final String redactedUri;

        public JavaObjectWithRedactedField(
                @JsonProperty(access = JsonProperty.Access.WRITE_ONLY)
                String uri
        ) {
            this.uri = uri;
            this.redactedUri = uri == null ? null : uri.replace("password", "***");
        }

        public String getUri() {
            return uri;
        }
    }

    private static class ConstructorParamNameIntrospector extends NopAnnotationIntrospector {
        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

        @Override
        public String findImplicitPropertyName(MapperConfig<?> config, AnnotatedMember member) {
            if (member instanceof AnnotatedParameter) {
                //
                return CONSTRUCTOR_PARAM_NAME;
            }
            return null;
        }
    }

    @Test
    public void test() {
        SimpleModule module = new SimpleModule() {
            @Override
            public void setupModule(SetupContext context) {
                context.appendAnnotationIntrospector(new ConstructorParamNameIntrospector());
            }
        };

        JsonMapper mapper = JsonMapper.builder()
                .addModule(module)
                .build();

        JavaObjectWithRedactedField original = new JavaObjectWithRedactedField("my-password");
        String json = mapper.writeValueAsString(original);
        System.out.println(json);

        JavaObjectWithRedactedField readValue = mapper.readValue(json, JavaObjectWithRedactedField.class);
        assertEquals(original.redactedUri, readValue.getUri());
    }
}
```

### Expected behavior

Deserialization should work.

### Additional context

This issue reproduces the following problem using only `Java`.
https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-module-kotlin/issues/1153

Consider class

```java
public class UserWithAnySetter {
    public String name;

    @JsonIgnore
    public String sensitiveField;

    @JsonAnySetter
    public Map<String, Object> extras = new HashMap<>();
}
```

reading content like so:

```java
    JsonMapper mapper = new JsonMapper();
    UserWithAnySetter u = mapper.readValue(
        "{\"name\":\"alice\",\"sensitiveField\":\"secret\",\"other\":\"val\"}",
        UserWithAnySetter.class);
```

will result in `sensitiveField` value getting passed to Any Setter: it should not: only "other" should be passed in this particular case.

