### Describe the bug

When having an attribute that starts with a single character, the second character of the serialized content by the `ObjectMapper` is not capitalized.

### Version Information

2.21.2

Note: worked on 2.19.2

### Reproduction

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;

public class Foo {

    @JsonProperty("xPropName")
    private String xPropName;

    public String getXPropName() {
        return this.xPropName;
    }

    public void setXPropName(String xPropName) {
        this.xPropName = xPropName;
    }
}
``` 

```java
void main() throws JsonProcessingException {
    Foo foo = new Foo();
    foo.setXPropName("some value");
    String result = new ObjectMapper().writeValueAsString(foo);
    System.out.println(result);
}
```

### Expected behavior


Expecting to have:

`{"xPropName":"some value"}`

Actually having:

`{"xpropName":"some value","xPropName":"some value"}`

Note: when removing the `@JsonProperty` annotation, I only get the `"xpropName"` property.

### Additional context

Tested with a jdk 21 and a jdk 25 (same results)

