### Describe the bug

When serializing enums on Jackson 3.x, it appears that relevant modules are never considered, and the enum value's `toString()` is used instead, so the enum values get serialized as `"SOME"` and `"VALUE"`.

This happens regardless of enabling or disabling `EnumFeature.READ_ENUMS_USING_TO_STRING`/`EnumFeature.WRITE_ENUMS_USING_TO_STRING`.




### Version Information

3.x

### Reproduction

In my codebase enum (de)serialization is guided via the use of a marker interface `IPersistenceKeyEnum`.

The json mapper is configured with a special `PersistenceKeyEnumsModule` ...

```
  private final JsonMapper jsonMapper = JsonMapper.builder()
      .addModule(new PersistenceKeyEnumsModule())
      .build();
```

... that has no relevant surprises and looks like this:

```
public final class PersistenceKeyEnumsModule extends JacksonModule {
  private final PersistenceKeyEnumSerializer serializer = new PersistenceKeyEnumSerializer();
  private final Map<Class<?>, PersistenceKeyEnumDeserializer> deserializerCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

  @Override
  public String getModuleName() {
    return getClass().getName();
  }

  @Override
  public Version version() {
    return Version.unknownVersion();
  }

  @Override
  public void setupModule(JacksonModule.SetupContext context) {
    context.addSerializers(new Serializers.Base() {
      @Override
      public ValueSerializer<?> findSerializer(
          SerializationConfig config, JavaType type, BeanDescription.Supplier beanDescRef, JsonFormat.Value formatOverrides) {
        // Make sure we could deserialize before offering to serialize.
        return findDeserializer(type.getRawClass()) != null
            ? serializer
            : null;
      }
    });
    context.addDeserializers(new Deserializers.Base() {
 ... yadda yadda yadda ...
```

... that checks whether the enum implements the interface.

If that's the case, serialization happens by calling the enum's `persistenceKey` method:

```
  private static final class PersistenceKeyEnumSerializer extends ToStringSerializerBase {

    private PersistenceKeyEnumSerializer() {
      super(IPersistenceKeyEnum.class);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean isEmpty(SerializationContext context, Object value) {
      return value == null;
    }

    @Override
    public String valueToString(Object value) {
      return ((IPersistenceKeyEnum) value).persistenceKey();
    }
  }
```


Deserialization happens analog to that, using either some amount of reflection or a static method with a fixed name.

Now consider a simple enum like this:

```
private enum MySimpleEnum implements IPersistenceKeyEnum {
  SOME("some"), VALUE("value");

  private final String persistenceKey;

  MySimpleEnum(String persistenceKey) {
    this.persistenceKey = persistenceKey;
  }

  public String persistenceKey() {
    return persistenceKey;
  }
}
```

### Expected behavior

Like on Jackson 2.x, if a module is configured, it should be consulted, probably regardless of (or in addition to) any other approaches configured via `JsonMapp`-global features, such that the enum values get serialized as `"some"` and `"value"`.

### Additional context

