### Describe the bug

Hi,

I am in the process of migrating an existing Spring boot application to version 4 which requires the migration from Jackson 2 to Jackson 3. The entire codebase was migrated to V3 without any issue thanks to the in depth migration guide provided by the Jackson team and community.
However, there is one particular test cases that keeps failing with an internal Jackson error when using a custom Deserializer that extends from `BeanDeserializer`. You can find a very simplified version of a unit test that demonstrates the problem.

We have a mechanisms in place with a custom deserializer that will additionally call custom converters conditionally after the default bean deserializing took place. The problem we now run into is the following:

```
tools.jackson.databind.exc.MismatchedInputException: Cannot construct instance of `org.example.CustomBeanDeserializerTest$Model` (although at least one Creator exists): cannot deserialize from Object value (no delegate- or property-based Creator)
 at [Source: REDACTED (`StreamReadFeature.INCLUDE_SOURCE_IN_LOCATION` disabled); byte offset: #UNKNOWN]
```

You can run below test code to reproduce the problem. Additionally, I tried setting up the JsonMapper with `builderWithJackson2Defaults` but than I run into another exception:

```
java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke "tools.jackson.core.sym.PropertyNameMatcher.matchName(String)" because "matcher" is null

	at tools.jackson.core.base.ParserMinimalBase.currentNameMatch(ParserMinimalBase.java:498)
	at tools.jackson.databind.deser.bean.BeanDeserializer.deserializeFromObject(BeanDeserializer.java:648)
	at tools.jackson.databind.deser.bean.BeanDeserializer.deserialize(BeanDeserializer.java:200)
	at org.example.CustomBeanDeserializerTest$CustomBeanDeserializer.deserialize(CustomBeanDeserializerTest.java:61)
	at tools.jackson.databind.deser.DeserializationContextExt.readRootValue(DeserializationContextExt.java:266)
	at tools.jackson.databind.ObjectReader._bindAndClose(ObjectReader.java:1888)

```

If you require any additional input, feel free to ask!

### Version Information

Jackson 3.1.0

### Reproduction

```
