### Describe the bug

The fix introduces for issue #650 breaks @JsonUnwrapped deserialization.
The merged fix introduces the following method in `UnrappedPropertyHandler`:
```java
private boolean _collectDeserializerPropertyNames(SettableBeanProperty prop, Set<String> names) {
    if (prop != null) {
        ValueDeserializer<?> deser = prop.getValueDeserializer();
        if (deser instanceof BeanDeserializerBase bd) {
            // Recursively collect property names
            bd.collectAllPropertyNamesTo(names);
            return bd.hasAnySetter();
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```
If the propery value deserializer is not a `BeanDeserializerBase`, then the unwrapped properties are not collected and the framework fails to rebuild the unwrapped value.
This is effectively restricting support to unwrapped objects to only types deserialized using `BeanDeserializerBase`.
Note that the current code also fails to deal with delegating deserializers, even if the delegatee ends up being a `BeanDeserializerBase`.
Note also that you need to enable the FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES feature to actually manifest the failure with an exception, otherwise the value will be silently deserialized with null values for the unwrapped properties.

I personally think that a better OO approach would have been to add the two new methods `collectAllPropertyNamesTo` and `hasAnySetter` to the `ValueDeserializer` class so that unwrapping can be properly supported for all deserializer not just POJO ones.

