If you have a polymorphic sub-type that you want to serialize in a custom serializer and you look up the `ValueSerializer` for the super-type via `SerializationContext::findTypedValueSerializer`, that returned serializer does not serialize the object completely. However, if you do the same for a collection type (e.g. `List<Supertype>`) or reference type (e.g. `Optional<Supertype>`), the serialized sub-type object is complete.

