### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.

The [migration documentation](https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson/blob/main/jackson3/MIGRATING_TO_JACKSON_3.md) does not state any pattern for replacing the combination of `JsonCreator` / `JsonValue`, strongly used with enum.

It may be solved by implementing a `EnumNamingStrategy`, as long as the value in the json is a string.

However, given the case where we want to specify (in open api for instance) that we have an enum with integers values . In java we would implement it like so

```java
 @EnumNaming(SongEnum.SongEnumNamingStrategy.class)
    public enum SongEnum {
